No cost meals are now available for all Methacton School District students.
Our current curbside service times are 7 AM – 9 AM and 11 AM – 1 PM on Tuesdays and Thursdays.
Tuesday’s pickup includes breakfast and lunch for Tuesday and Wednesday.
Thursday’s pickup includes breakfast and lunch for Thursday, Friday and Monday.
For more information: http://ow.ly/6JIh30r8YPY

post_text: In case you missed it, check out some exciting NEWS from the Methacton Education Foundation that made the News!
shared_text:
Methacton Education Foundation
July 9 at 10:31 PM ·

6abc Action News was on hand today as we received a $4,000 donation from Indian Americans for Covid-19 Relief PA!!

Rick Williams reports that this coalition of 25 organizations from the Indian Hindu Community has helped thousands across Eastern Pennsylvania.

This donation to the Methacton COVID-19 Relief Fund will help provide easy-to-prepare summer meals to Methacton students who don’t have enough to eat at home.

Join us in thanking the Indian-Americans for COVID-19 Relief!!!
Thank you!!!

#OneMethacton #ClimbHigher
#MethactonPride Methacton
Methacton School District

post_text: We’re ONE HOUR AWAY from the unveiling of the Philadelphia Zoo’s UNLESS Contest winners! Arrowhead & Woodland Elementary Schools are FINALISTS in the competition. The winners will be announced on the Philadelphia Zoo's Facebook page at 2pm! Good luck Arrowhead & Woodland!
shared_text:
Philadelphia Zoo
May 15 at 3:13 PM ·

We're excited to announce the FINALISTS for this year's Albert M. Greenfield Foundation UNLESS Contest! We're so proud of these students for their work protecting endangered species and finding ways humans and wildlife can #ThriveTogether! Find out who wins on #PhillyZooAt2!

post_text: Join Mallon Planetarium Director Mr. Chantry for a LIVE SKY TOUR TONIGHT!
shared_text:
Live Sky Tour (Wed. 5/13) 8:45

Methacton's Mallon Planetarium was live.
May 13 at 2:05 PM ·

Getting close! Already spotted Venus through my telescope. Dress warm and find a spot near your house away from lights and trees!

Dress up WARM, go out in your own backyard, and get a live tour of the night sky from the director of Methacton's Mallon Planetarium, Adam Chantry here on Facebook Live!
Mr. Chantry will help you identify the bright stars (and planet) in our evening sky, identify the constellations overhead, and show you where to point binoculars (if you have them).
All this in your own yard!

post_text: Congratulations to Arrowhead & Woodland Elementary Schools for earning a FINALIST spot in the Philadelphia Zoo’s UNLESS Contest. The winners will be announced LIVE on the Philadelphia Zoo's Facebook page on Friday, 5/15 at 2pm! The UNLESS Contest challenges and empowers students to make a positive change for wildlife. Our student participants chose to save the Golden Lion Tamarin from extinction as their cause. Make sure to tune in!
text: Congratulations to Arrowhead & Woodland Elementary Schools for earning a FINALIST spot in the Philadelphia Zoo’s UNLESS Contest. The winners will be announced LIVE on the Philadelphia Zoo's Facebook page on Friday, 5/15 at 2pm! The UNLESS Contest challenges and empowers students to make a positive change for wildlife. Our student participants chose to save the Golden Lion Tamarin from extinction as their cause. Make sure to tune in!

post_text: Congratulations to Team Arcola! They are the regional winners of the Chemical Educational Foundation’s “You Be The Chemist” Challenge. The team-based competition allows students to collaborate to explore science concepts and elevates STEM careers. More than 36,000 students from 451 schools participated in the challenge this year.
shared_text:
Chemical Educational Foundation & You Be The Chemist
May 6 at 9:56 PM ·

The 2019-2020 #YouBeTheChemist Challenge state and regional winners have been announced! Congratulations to all teams for their hard work. See the full list of winners here: https://www.chemed.org/2019-2020-challenge-winners/

Methacton Education Foundation
March 12 at 2:02 AM ·

We are very disappointed to inform you, per the district email earlier this evening canceling all large gatherings and activities including outside groups, that the Methacton Dodgeball Tournament scheduled for March 21st, has been postponed.

This is an evolving situation and we appreciate your patience as we work to reschedule the Dodgeball Tournament. We will work closely with the District and follow the Health Department’s recommendations to ensure a safe and fun event.

We will let you know when we have secured a new date for the Dodgeball Tournament. In the meantime, please visit our website or follow us on Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter.

Thank you for your patience and support.

We will let you know when we have secured a new date for the Dodgeball Tournament. In the meantime, please visit our website or follow us on Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter.

Thank you for your patience and support.

post_text:
What an INCREDIBLE year for Methacton Athletics!

Congratulations to Kibwe McNair (Class of 2020) and Roman Moser (Class of 2020) for representing Methacton in the State Championships for wrestling. Moser was eliminated after his first consolation match. He finishes his Methacton wrestling career with 98 victories. McNair was eliminated in the 2nd consolation round. He finishes his Methacton career as a 3-time state qualifier, a District and Regional champion, and with 129 wins!

Congratulations to Tommy Gibbs (Class of 2022) for qualifying for the State Championships in the 100 Yard Butterfly! The championship games will take place March 11 and March 12 at Bucknell University in Lewisburg, PA.

Fox 29’s Traffic Anchor Bob Kelly is bringing his Kelly’s Classroom live broadcast to Worcester Elementary School on February 11, 2020. Tune in to Fox 29’s Good Day Philadelphia from 9am to 10am to see Worcester Elementary School celebrate the 100th Day of School with their annual 1st Grade Fashion Show. You don’t want to miss all the fun!

For a behind-the-scenes look at the live broadcast, be sure to give “Bob Kelly Fox29” a “like” on Facebook. And while you’re there, “like” the “Methacton School District” Facebook page so you can always keep up with the latest news and information about the great things going on in our district.

post_text: Worcester Student Council Advisors, Stephanie Cohen and Regina Shanaman, accompanied 20 third and fourth grade Student Council members on their 13th Annual Holiday Shopping Trip to Target in North Wales on Monday, December 9th. There were 8 parent chaperones and one Instructional Assistant also in attendance. The students were split into four groups to shop for four Methacton Families. The students were given a list of wants and needs to purchase for each of the 14 children who were “adopted.” Students purchased clothing, shoes, toys, books and games to help make their holidays a little more bountiful. While the students and chaperones were shopping, Mrs. Cohen and Mrs. Shanaman were filling carts with holiday meal items and food for the week that the children will be home from school. Student Council used funds that they raised during Smencil pencil sales as well as the November Conference Bake Sale to fund the trip. See more photos here: http://ow.ly/c2y950xzwAh

post_text: Skyview Upper Elementary School Special Education Teacher Stacy McGowan helped organize a wonderful surprise for one of her students. She secured a “travel chair” for 5th grader PJ that will allow his family more flexibility to travel with him, but the chair was not in our area. The chair was available at the non-profit United Cerebral Palsy (UCP) near Harrisburg -- but Ms. McGowan had no way of getting out there to pick it up. She called the Office of PA St. Rep. Matt Bradford and explained her dilemma. Rep. Bradford’s office graciously offered to pick up the chair and personally delivered it to PJ at Skyview Upper Elementary School this morning. Go to http://ow.ly/VXS230q13xc for a slideshow of the heartwarming event.

post_text: The Methacton Board of School Directors held its reorganization meeting on December 2. Montgomery County Common Pleas Court Judge Thomas Rogers administered the oath of office to Kim Aubrey-Larcinese, Andrew Maginnis, Andrea Rees, Semira Perdue, and Paul Winters. Ms. Aubrey-Larcinese, Ms. Rees, and Mr. Winters are returning members of the Board; Mr. Maginnis and Ms. Perdue are newly-elected members. They join seated Board members Jen Cancro, Elizabeth Drummond, Mary Hull, and Ralph Navarrete. Watch the swearing-in at http://www.methacton.org/boardvideos
